annotationA: U1 small nuclear ribonucleoprotein A; Binds stem loop II of U1 snRNA. It is the first snRNP to interact with pre-mRNA. This interaction is required for the subsequent binding of U2 snRNP and the U4/U6/U5 tri-snRNP (By similarity). Plays a role in regulating sex-lethal splicing; Belongs to the RRM U1 A/B'' family
annotationB: Cell division cycle 5, isoform A; DNA binding; chromatin binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: mRNA splicing, via spliceosome; centrosome duplication
